Graduated college (B.A. in Media Communications and Elementary Education) and became a Flight Attendant for United Airlines so I could travel the world for free and meet new people.  

Eventually, I settled down and became a classroom teacher for many years.  After being recruited by an educational company, Lakeshore Learning, I entered the corporate world of education and became the Regional Elementary Sales Manager for the AZ/NM territory.  After a couple of years, Lakeshore transitioned me into the role of a Professional Development Specialist.  As a PD Specialist, I developed, planned, and executed professional development trainings for teachers/school districts across the US.  I traveled the majority of time as the trainings were live and in-person, while about 20% of the trainings were done virtually.  

Once the pandemic hit, I was unable to travel for trainings and the company was partially shutdown.  So, having an active AZ real estate license for my personal investment properties, I kicked it into full gear. 
I partnered with Keller Williams and sold over $10M in 2021!  I'm looking to surpass that in 2022.  I did continue with Lakeshore as a consultant throughout the pandemic, but eventually I needed to choose where I was going to focus my time and energy, so I stayed with real estate.

I have zero franchise experience.  Just a ton of motivation, positive energy, and skills to fulfill my life-long dream of owning a business.  Hoping to learn more about Dirty Dough to see if we're a good fit!

Professional Experience:
Jeff Manning: 

After completing missionary service for my church, I continued in the path of service by pursuing a career as a professional firefighter. I have devoted my professional life to public service as an employee at one of the busiest fire departments in the nation. 
 
Through my years of service to the Las Vegas community, I have promoted through the ranks of paramedic, firefighter, engineer, and will be wrapping up my career as a Fire Captain. 
 
As a Fire Captain, I am responsible for the rapid mitigation of emergencies. These emergencies range from medical calls, mass casualty incidents, structure fires, and in recent years the mitigation of active shooter incidents. 
 
Stabilization of large scale incidents has given me unique experiences that have shaped me as an individual and prepared me for my next journey. As I move closer towards retirement I am excited to start my transition our of the fire service and into the cookie business.
 
I have obtained degrees in Paramedic medicine, Fire Science, and finished with a management degree from BYU. While I absolutely love the fire service, I am ready to utilize what I have learned to serve a  community in a different role with the addition of a great franchise and work environment for our future employees

Josh Fernandez:
  
   I grew up in the Midwest and as a young man decided to devote 2 years of my life to missionary work. As a missionary I was assigned to Las Vegas where I eventually returned after my missionary service and have remained for nearly 22 years. 
 
Las Vegas has provided career opportunities that have served as platforms for personal character and management development. I have spent the last 8 years working in the tech industry for a large privately owned data management center. As an employee at SWITCH, I have promoted through several ranks to my current position as a documentation and training developer.
 
Additionally, I have continued in my service to my church which has truly added to my personal growth and shown me what effective leadership is all about.

I love the community of Las Vegas and look forward to being a part of growing Dirty Dough into Nevada. Additionally, we desire to own several locations in our hometown with plans to build a team that will allow expansion into other markets.
 
I find tremendous fulfillment in providing for my family as they mean everything to me. I am extremely excited at the prospect of joining the Dirty Dough family and sincerely look forward to expanding their reach to other states.
 
It's a journey that I'm excited about doing with my wife, daughter, and my Brother-in-Law's family. I appreciate your time reviewing our application.

column15:
Tell us about your professional experience
 
I have been in the restaurant and bar industry for over 18 years. I have held multiple positions in that time with the highest being director of operations and with revenues exceeding 50 million per year. I have also owned 2 small businesses outside of the restaurant industry. My business partner and I are currently interested in restaurant franchises and we love the Dirty Dough business model.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
I heard about dirty dough on the franchise secrets podcast that I listen to. It caught my attention cause I am very familiar with the crumbl cookie business model and thought this would be worth looking into and learning more about the business.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
The business model and the brand are 2 of the things that initially interested me. I know that other businesses in this Felipe’s do very well and I think it is a successful business model.
Have you visited our store before?
 
No
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
500k plus
What are your plans for funding?
 
Private funding or SBA
What is your current liquidity?
 
1 million plus
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
I plan on being an owner operator and would like to open multiple stores based on the market demand.
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Las Vegas, nv. Henderson, nv. Scottsdale, az.
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
2
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
I have a little background in marketing which would help but I also have connections in the marketing field that I would hire to do SEO, social media and any other marketing needed to create brand awareness. I also have a large local following from working in restaurants and bars for that last 18 years that would help support the business.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
My business partner has been in commercial real estate for the last 30 years and has actually helped develop shopping centers and funded a few QSR restaurants in nevada.
He is looking at doing a partnership with Jason and Alan in Hawaii, but for now they are interested in Gillette WY.

He lives here in Lehi, Utah. He is an IT engineer. Interested in North Carolina. Just got married in December.
Tell us about your professional experience
 	I work as an Sr.Web Systems Engineer at Verisk analytics. I have created an IOS and Android mobile app called "DumbshellArts" and it is doing well in Android version. I am very much interested to start a business, work hard, earn respect.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 	I heard about Dirty Dough through my friend. No, I am not related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 	I went and tasted the cookies and I loved the taste of each bite of cookie. I feel there is a magic in it.
Have you visited our store before?
 	Yes
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 	No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 	No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 	150k
What are your plans for funding?
 	Loan from bank or credit union
What is your current liquidity?
 	60k
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 	I want to work as employee and take care of store. Want to greet, welcome the people who comes to store with laugh and positive vibes.
Will you have a partner?
 	No
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 	
1. Orem, UT 2. Lehi, UT. 3. Raleigh, NC
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 	1
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 	Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 	Social media plays a vital role in marketing world. I will open the local Dirty Dough store accounts in different social media platforms like Facebook, Instagram, Twitter etc and connects to public. Also, will visit to corporate offices and do publicity by telling about the taste of Dirty Dough cookies.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 	I will analyze the below points and take a calculated move to open a top tier Dirty Dough store. Enclosed shopping malls, Open-air shopping centers, Neighborhood grocer/drug store center, Pedestrian areas, such as downtown shopping streets, Freestanding kiosks or carts, Are there enough potential customers nearby?, Is the space accessible?, Is it move-in ready?, What are the neighbors like?, What are the local zoning restrictions?, Is the infrastructure adequate?, What is included in the rent?, Is it safe?, What are the lease terms?

Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?

Everything from formal networking events, social clubs (Rotary/Kiwanis), and even local festivals and parades. I am really only interested in the mobile trailer franchise (at least at first) and the success there comes from being present at events in the public eye.

You find those through community connections, county event calendars, church events, school events, and neighborhood connections. If I had to have a physical store location I have a friend who is a SBA lender that also has a commercial real estate license. I would probably start on Loopnet.com and work with him on the details.

Tell us about your professional experience
 
Currently an Enterprise sales professional at Atlassian, a top tech company in the world. Have done real estate investing including 15 flip projects, 5 rentals, as well as building and selling a small real estate renovations/maintenance company.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
I currently live in Utah and heard of Dirty Dough through the Utah Cookie Wars.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
I love food and have had a sweet tooth for years, so getting into something in this industry has been on my mind for a while. Listening to Bennett's episode on 'Franchise Secrets' really made me admire the business and financial philosophy that Dirty Dough is built on, as well as the mission to bring imperfection and relatability to the consumers.
Have you visited our store before?
 
Yes

No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
$340,000
What are your plans for funding?
 
SBA Loan
What is your current liquidity?
 
$165,000
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
We plan to be physically present in the store working alongside hired staff running the actual shop, as well as doing in person visits to all of the local businesses and corporations in the immediate vicinity of the shop location.
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Portland, OR
Seattle, WA
Las Vegas, NV
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
One store initially with the hopes of opening minimally another 1-2 in the next year after.
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
Our main efforts to increase brand awareness and local marketing will be by performing local fundraisers and community events with non-profits and schools, identify sponsorship opportunities with local sports teams, and direct marketing to nearby business in the immediate vicinity for corporate events.

We also intend to run customer loyalty rewards/programs and birthday clubs.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
We are both intimately familiar with the Portland, Seattle, and Las Vegas metro areas. We intend to drive this process by networking with local business owners in each market to identify the best areas and neighborhoods, hire a professional commercial real estate broker to provide us additional demographic and pricing insight, as well as perform our our research of various factors like accessibility to the shop location, operating costs, and average income, age, and household sizes.

column15:
Tell us about your professional experience
 
Pharmacy Regional Leader. I have been in the pharmaceutical industry now for about 10 years and have absolutely loved it. I have a region that covers all of idaho, eastern Oregon, and a couple spots in Washington. My job is to keep pharmacies open and promote profits through healthcare services such as immunizations, prescription management, clinics services, while also partnering with my retail store regional manager to collaborate and promote front end business as well. Being a pharmacist has been an absolute pleasure and I love what I do.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
I initially heard about it through LinkedIn last year and have been following the business ever since. I try to pay attention to the news regarding Dirty Dough and have enjoyed the ride so far.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
One thing that struck a chord with me was the mental health focus. When I was in pharmacy school, I came across a 12 year old girl in the hospital ER who had attempted suicide. In her charts there were some extremely sad statements that have stuck with me for quite some time. Bullying and home support were two main topics that she felt were out of place. I’ve even started writing children’s books with a bit of an agenda… focusing on those who can find support in unlikely places. So far, I’m three books in  
That was a huge draw to this company. This particular industry has excited my family for ages, and to see a company with such a fantastic image combined with an amazing focus, it was a no brainer.
Have you visited our store before?
 
Yes
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
0 (student loans and mortgage take this down)
What are your plans for funding?
 
Financing
What is your current liquidity?
 
20k
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
I would like this to be my main focus. At first, probably 75% me, 25% partner
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Meridian, ID
Boise, ID
Eagle, ID
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
1
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
Utilizing the mental health aspect of this business to make people more aware of the background focus. We have many hospital systems that I am affiliated with that can influence awareness. Local adds and independent retailers that want to see this brand and its story. Utilizing social media and getting a huge footprint within the universities here (Boise State University, College of Idaho, and Idaho State University).
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
Partnering with some commercial real estate individuals and identifying/targeting high foot traffic locations surrounded by traveling conveniences. Meridian especially is growing like crazy and there are a lot of locations that have these exact characteristics.

Tell us about your professional experience
 
I have operated businesses and managed teams. I have worked in sales for 7 years and have experience working with restaurants. I have invested in real estate with a couple of rentals with my wife, crypto, and a couple of other small business ventures with some partners.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
I heard about you through LinkedIn and different posts from folks in my network commenting on the recent spat that has developed with Crumbl!
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
I love cookies! I wanted to franchise with Crumbl but after seeing how they are reacting to some health competition from you guys I decided to withdraw my application from their team and look into helping you grow!
Have you visited our store before?
 
Yes
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
$125,000
What are your plans for funding?
 
I have a network of partners and investors that I will be able to work with in getting additional funding once I have more data and plan to go off of.
What is your current liquidity?
 
$70,000
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
I can be 100% involved during that time and maintain high involvement moving forward as my vocation is a remote position.
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Utah, Hawaii, and Colorado
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
As many as the business can allow us to open. In the first year we would be looking to open one and if the market is favorable, we would want to expand before the fiscal year has passed.
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
I carry a lot of experience networking with local groups and community leaders through charity work I have conducted and fundraising. I have over 2 years of experience in growing partnership networks to enable hyper-growth and would look to bring those skills to my franchise. I also have seen a lot of success working with local influencers on social media.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
I'd conduct a heavy amount of research looking at target audiences, demographic data, and sales metrics to determine high performing locations and then look to duplicate the positioning, population, and economic conditions in areas I would like to start in to determine where we'd open.

column15:
Tell us about your professional experience
 
B2B distribution and channel management including managing volume and margin, influencing/directing sales people, and engineering solutions for customers.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
Wade Rasmussen interviewed on this podcast: https://themidnightfounderspodcast.podbean.com/
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
First, Wentzville, Missouri is a prime spot for growth and culture for eateries. Would love to tell you more about that. Would love to beat Crumbl and show how their “trademark” infringement claims are nonsense. Dirty dough has the brains behind the business model to impress customers with simplified operations. Having supported prairie farms and their mass-produced ice cream operations, in addition to several other food and beverage manufactures (Anheuser-Busch), I’d like to play big with a small company and grow the catering and customer revenue streams.
Have you visited our store before?
 
Yes
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
250,000
What are your plans for funding?
 
Bank/note funding as needed
What is your current liquidity?
 
Equities, crypto, cash
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
I’d like to implement the E-Myth Revisited strategy of clarifying roles and Responsibilities for each team member, articulate a vision for employees, and create an attractive culture of hard work and (safe) fun.
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Wentzville, Missouri
Lake Saint Louis, Missouri
Troy, Missouri
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
1
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
Catering (dial for dollars), community events that we create like “Dough with Dads” that celebrates the relationships that fathers are creating with their kids by spending time together and enjoying the best sweet treats together.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
Network, Google AdWords (including by geography), ease of access, and am probably going to propose a food truck to support events, and expand your reach to Troy and Lake St Louis from Wentzville.

Tell us about your professional experience
 
Currently retired but spent approximately 12 years retail with Children's Clothing store followed by more than years forming and leading a private non -profit Agency contracting with state of Texas.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
My daughter told me about your store as we discussed a competitor’s product and availability.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
Opportunity in an untapped Marley with a product I enjoy personally as well as franchise available smaller markets. Low need for high lAbor costs also a plus in markets with limited work force.
Have you visited our store before?
 
No
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
Over 2 million
What are your plans for funding?
 
Personal
What is your current liquidity?
 
Over 500,000
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
We live in both communities half of year and would want to know all aspects of business well and be in business often as faces in community. We would want much involvement.
Will you have a partner?
 
No
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Lago vista, Texas; Angel Fire, New Mexico Tyler, Texas
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
Up to 2, 1 per year
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
Social media, mail outs, community events and support
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
Local real estate agents and commercial research

column15:
Tell us about your professional experience
 
I am the CEO & Co-Founder of a marketing agency called Scroll. My wife and I are "chronically" entrepreneurs. We are obsessed with our home town of Davis County & think it deserves the best options for everyone to enjoy!
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
I am not related to anyone. I honestly heard about Dirty Dough through the law suit & have become a massive fan in the process.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
I think Davis County needs a Dirty Dough because it's options are so slim. It would be a massive opportunity & I want to own it before anyone else can!
Have you visited our store before?
 
Yes
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
$300k-$500k
What are your plans for funding?
 
Franchise fee's paid up front and financing anything else
What is your current liquidity?
 
$100k
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
We could be involved in training and involved in the store part time. We also could have our spouses involved in the store daily!
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Davis County! Weber County, Farmington/Layton
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
1 Store for now but would love to help build the brand over time.
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
Yes
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
We have a strong local presence with our families and friends so we could do a big grand opening & big events with local companies. We would do well with small businesses here and building the pipeline with corporate gifts. We also own a digital marketing agency and can do a lot of work with Google My Business and Social Media!
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
Looking for other food options close by. Lots of foot traffic near by. Also looking for population that is close by so we can know if we are in good radius for delivery.

How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
Our son heard about it on social media. He is graduating from college this December, but is also already working as a licensed realtor with me. He has been researching business ideas with/for us. Our plan is to hopefully find a business idea for us to get into, now, and then he can come into the same business when his finances are established.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
We believe the Texas market is ripe for your concept/product. We have identified locations that we believe will be highly profitable. After researching, online, your process seems sustainable and more than competitive.

No

We have already identified geographic areas. I sell residential and commercial

column15:
Tell us about your professional experience
 
I am a professional geologist and environmental consultant. I have been in environmental consulting since getting my Masters Degree in Geology in 2019. Prior to that, I taught college bowling and racquetball courses. At my current job, I regularly work with clients to solve their environmental problems, minimize risk, and reduce liability. I also manage projects, including schedules, budgets, and client expectations. My wife also runs a bakery out of our home and has a business degree in information systems. She has managed her books, managed invoicing, and kept regular inventory on supplies. She will be my partner in business.
How did you hear about Dirty Dough? Are you related to any Dirty Dough corporate employee or franchisee?
 
I am active on LinkedIn, have been a long-time fan/follower of Crumbl, and have since learned about Dirty Dough and started following Bennett Maxwell. I have learned about Dirty Dough's product and mission and would like to be a part of that. We are not related to any Dirty Dough employees or franchisees.
What interested you most in pursuing franchising with Dirty Dough?
 
What piqued our interest is the opportunity to provide a quality product to a booming market in need near our home. We also want to learn and grow professionally and provide opportunities for work to the youth in our area. We want to serve other people by providing them with quality products.
Have you visited our store before?
 
No
Do you currently or have you ever been affiliated with any other franchises?
 
No
We conduct a credit and background check. Have you ever been convicted of a crime?
 
No
What is your net worth (assets - liabilities)?
 
~$220000
What are your plans for funding?
 
On top of our contribution, my father (net worth ~$9 million) is looking to diversify his assets and invest into this business
What is your current liquidity?
 
$15000
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
Kristin (my wife) and I will both be actively operating at the beginning. Kristin will be the main owner operator for day-to-day operations, and I will be a part-time operator. We intend on setting up systems to manage scheduling, accounting/payroll, inventory, etc. ourselves.
Will you have a partner?
 
Yes
List your TOP 3 territories (City, State) for opening a store
 
Katy, Texas
Conroe, Texas
San Antonio, Texas
How many stores are you interested in? If more than one, how many are you planning to open in year 1?
 
One store for year 1, more in the future
Are you open to other territories if your top 3 aren’t available?
 
No
Dirty Dough does the digital marketing for franchisees, however, you will be required to market in the community. Tell us how you plan to increase brand awareness and local marketing?
 
Social Media Marketing will be a large focus for us. If in our area of residence, we plan on marketing through my wife's bakery, Good Home Sweets, as well as through word of mouth through contacts, church members, and school associates. We plan to sponsor/participate in local farmers markets, fundraising events, and food drives. We will physically attend local events and community activities to market in person.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
Our area in Katy is booming with new housing developments. We plan to research projected growth in Katy, study traffic patterns, and determine where a good balance between convenience, target market, and affordability is.

First of all, My family and I we love Dirty Dough's cookies!
I've seen Dirty Dough growing in a very fast pace.
Comparing it with other cookie brands, Dirty Dough has a better built-in support system in managing daily tasks.

Dirty dough has a great profit margins.

Yes

No

No

70,000

I have a family member that would like to partnership with me and put the remaining amount 140k+ to be able to open the store.
What is your current liquidity?
 
40,000
Dirty Dough does not require you to be an owner operator, we do require you to be present for the first 3 weeks of opening. Tell us how involved you plan on being?
 
I would be completely involved the first 3 weeks. I would plan to become an owner operator too.

Yes

Eagle Mountain
Saratoga Springs
Bluffdale

I am planning to open just one for now

Yes

I know renown marketers that can help me increasing the brand awareness in my area.

I plan to do a grand opening and give free cookies.
I plan to buy trucks where we can wrap them with the Logo of Dirty Dough.
How do you plan on finding top tier locations for your store?
 
I plan to be next to school/recreational/restaurant areas.
